Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

Since we don't have a release-notes.yaml on the dependency, I think we need one here.  I guess the change is that some locations-related PATCH calls that used to succeed, and which could produce anomalous behavior, will now result in a 409?

Patch Set 3:

> Since we don't have a release-notes.yaml on the dependency, I think
 > we need one here.  I guess the change is that some
 > locations-related PATCH calls that used to succeed, and which could
 > produce anomalous behavior, will now result in a 409?

Yeah (good catch). I've got them covered here at https://review.openstack.org/#/c/366973/ . We need plenty more updated to the release notes so trying to get them done in the same page.

See the poor rendering of the unreleased release notes at http://docs.openstack.org/releasenotes/glance/unreleased.html

Patch Set 3: Code-Review+2

Given Ie463e2f30db94cde7716c83a94ec2fb0c0658c91 I think it makes sense to update the version of Glance API that's current versus supported.

That said, I think our versioning is potentially flawed in that someone will see a 409 regardless of whether they use 2.0, 2.1, 2.2, 2.3, or 2.4. We might need to start to develop something to fix that.

Patch Set 3:

> Since we don't have a release-notes.yaml on the dependency, I think

Yeah, this is the one that needs this bump https://review.openstack.org/324012

But there's going to be another likely to merge https://review.openstack.org/366995

I'm in the process of collecting all changes that need release notes and complete the notes on this patch https://review.openstack.org/366973

If the above proposal is okay, can we move towards merging it?
